# Victorian Era (1837–1901)

The **Victorian era** was the period of [Queen Victoria](/Queen_Victoria)'s reign from **20 June 1837** until her death on **22 January 1901**. This era followed the [Georgian era](/Georgian_era) and preceded the [Edwardian era](/Edwardian_era), with its later half overlapping with the first part of the [Belle Époque](/Belle_%C3%89poque) in continental Europe.

The Victorian era was a time of significant change in the [United Kingdom](/United_Kingdom) and the [British Empire](/British_Empire), marked by industrial, cultural, political, scientific, and military developments. It saw the expansion of the British Empire, the Industrial Revolution reaching its peak, and the emergence of modern British society.

---

## **Queen Victoria and Her Reign**

[Queen Victoria](/Queen_Victoria) ascended to the throne at the age of 18, following the death of her uncle, [William IV](/William_IV_of_the_United_Kingdom). Her reign lasted **63 years and seven months**, making her the longest-reigning British monarch until [Elizabeth II](/Elizabeth_II) surpassed her in 2015.

### **Key Political Leaders of the Era**
- **[The Viscount Melbourne](/William_Lamb,_2nd_Viscount_Melbourne)** (Whig, 1837–1841)
- **[Sir Robert Peel](/Robert_Peel)** (Conservative, 1841–1846)
- **[Lord John Russell](/John_Russell,_1st_Earl_Russell)** (Whig/Liberal, 1846–1852, 1865–1866)
- **[The Earl of Derby](/Edward_Smith-Stanley,_14th_Earl_of_Derby)** (Conservative, 1852, 1858–1859, 1866–1868)
- **[The Earl of Aberdeen](/George_Hamilton-Gordon,_4th_Earl_of_Aberdeen)** (Peelite/Conservative, 1852–1855)
- **[The Viscount Palmerston](/Henry_John_Temple,_3rd_Viscount_Palmerston)** (Liberal, 1855–1858, 1859–1865)
- **[Benjamin Disraeli](/Benjamin_Disraeli)** (Conservative, 1868, 1874–1880)
- **[William Ewart Gladstone](/William_Ewart_Gladstone)** (Liberal, 1868–1874, 1880–1885, 1886, 1892–1894)
- **[The Marquess of Salisbury](/Robert_Gascoyne-Cecil,_3rd_Marquess_of_Salisbury)** (Conservative, 1885–1886, 1886–1892, 1895–1902)
- **[The Earl of Rosebery](/Archibald_Primrose,_5th_Earl_of_Rosebery)** (Liberal, 1894–1895)

